annotations:
I’m not dancing, I’m fighting
 I’m not shining, I’m burning
 I’m not touching, I’m feeling
 I’m not dancing, I’m fighting

The entire song likely serves as an allution to the 1957 poem “Not Waving but Drowning” by famous British poet and novelist Stevie Smith.

The song borrows the structure of the title, which is also the most integral part of the poem itself, where a percieved positive situation is in actuality an internal struggle for the protagonist.
